message: Yes, there is a connection between the El, Bey, Al, Ali, and Dey Morris last names. These last names are associated with the Moorish Nation, which is a group of people of African and Arab descent who trace their ancestry to the Moors of North Africa. The Moorish Nation is recognized by the United States government as a sovereign nation, and its members are considered to be Indigenous people. The Moorish Nation is also recognized by the United Nations Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples (UNDRIP).
